author: DeAnn Komanecky
title: UPDATE: Toddler killed in Effingham wreck
text:
By DeAnn Komanecky A small child has died in an Oct. 19 accident on U.S. 80 near George Road in Effingham County.
The wreck occurred about 6:15 a.m. when a Chevy Malibu struck the rear of a log truck, Georgia State Patrol Trooper Colin Wheeler said.
The log truck was stopped in the roadway to turn left into the log yard.
One adult female and two juvenile males were in the car, Wheeler said.
The child killed was a passenger in the car. He was under 2 years old.
Also in the car were one adult female and another juvenile male.
All were transported to an area hospital.
The identity of the deceased child has not been released.
All family members have been notified, however, Wheeler said. The names should be released by Wednesday.
The accident continues to be investigated by the Georgia State Patrol.
